INSTITUTE FOR ART AND OLFACTION
2
MATERIALS REFERENCE DATABASE
3
PURPOSE OF DATABASE: This database shares information on what is stocked at the Institute for Art and Olfaction's experimental perfume studio in Los Angeles. We do not guarantee the accuracy of the data. It is shared for online reference-only, not for downloading. We encourage all perfumers, studios, labs and artists to create their own version that is reflective of their materials and needs.
4
TERMS OF SHARING: We share this dataset under a Creative Commons CC BY-NC license. This license includes the following elements: BY – Credit must be given to the creator NC – Only noncommercial uses of the work are permitted.
Summary: This license allows reusers to distribute, remix, adapt, and build upon the material in any medium or format for noncommercial purposes only, and only so long as attribution is given to the creator.
5
IMPORTANT: It is our shared responsibility to work safely, and ensure our own health and that of the people we share our work with. We have not included toxicity and IFRA restriction data in this dataset, but remind all visitors that some materials are toxic, and can cause a whole range of reactions including dermal sensitivities, neurological reactions, poinsoning, and in some cases very serious health hazards. Please be a responsible maker, and review all IFRA recommendations for materials you carry in your organ. Please also download and review all the materials safety data for each material you order (including flash point and toxicity reports.) Search the IFRA standards library: https://ifrafragrance.org/safe-use/library
